Congress approves Mifid transposition, which came into force on 1 November
In parallel to its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the Congress' vote of amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim of its entry into force before the end of the year.
Representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by MEPs and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation to ensure the protection of investors and to regulate in detail the activities of organizations so that markets function effectively.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernization of financial markets, at a time when it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial consultancy services for both specialised social and legal persons and creates a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial consultancy companies (FIAs), which merge securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to the regulated secondary markets multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems, which face competition from current exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment services firms to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all operations they perform, to facilitate control by the CNMV.
Passing through the Congressional Economic Commission, several amendments have been added, including one that highlights that the debt held will be considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has proven itself with what happened with the (high-priced) US mortgage debt.
In addition, they took advantage of the implementation of the management has taken advantage of legally delimiting the functions that graduates in Economics can have 30 years after, in 1977, was approved, the Royal Decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work on behalf of a company, who will not require the authorization of the CNMV, and who will be able to lend its product marketing and customer attraction services to different investment firms at the same time.
