What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible damages, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the driver's license, the civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use it is made, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return it becomes liable for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, driver's license age, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the odds to pay.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower rate of damages due to their precautionary nature.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
It is for this reason that the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that, in addition to adapting to the insurer's characteristics, it offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 have to face various drawbacks when entering into an affordable insurance contract, such as low driving experience and a driver’s license’s seniority.
Although the ideal to be well insured is a risk-free insurance, other more economical options exist.
The most foreseeable drivers can opt for any risk insurance with franchise, so that they get the coverage of any risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
“The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be determined based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower,” says Luis Noguera, Spain’s head of First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damages caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against the theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be cautious and avoid damages as far as possible, as this will have an impact on the bonus, which may reduce the price of the insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the base rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
"Bonus and penalties will depend on the company and its profits.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses,” clarifies Noguera.
Over the age of 25, this becomes easier for drivers at the time of entering into a contract with an insurance company, since the rate of damages is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is better to choose a risk insurance with deductible.
"Normally, young people can't benefit from the experience previously acquired after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better that he negotiates insurance at all risk, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the persons with the lowest claims rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be any risk insurance with deductible (may be 300 euros), or an extended third party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have a more relaxed drive and they have a greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of assuming a larger amount of franchises,” Judge Luis Noguera said.
For pensioners, a full-risk insurance with deductible is preferable (being 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, that is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us best according to our personal situation.
